PCI, PCMCIA, Flash, etc. Bit 0 Reserved Bit 1 Reserved Bit 2 Unknown Bit 3 BIOS Characteristics Not Supported Bit 4 ISA is supported Bit 5 MCA is supported Bit 6 EISA is supported Bit 7 PCI is supported Bit 8 PCMCIA is supported Bit 9 Plug and Play is supported Bit 10 APM is supported Bit 11 BIOS is Upgradeable (Flash) Bit 12 BIOS shadowing is allowed Bit 13 VL-VESA is supported Bit 14 ESCD support is available Bit 15 Boot from CD is supported Bit 16 Selectable Boot is supported Bit 17 BIOS ROM is socketed Bit 18 Boot From PCMCIA is supported Bit 19 EDD (Enhanced Disk Drive) Specification is supported Bit 20 Int 13h - Japanese Floppy for NEC 9800 1.2mb (3.5 inch, 1k Bytes/Sector, 360 RPM) is supported Bit 21 Int 13h - Japanese Floppy for Toshiba 1.2mb (3.5 inch, 360 RPM) is supported Bit 22 Int 13h - 5.25 inch / 360 KB Floppy Services are supported Bit 23 Int 13h - 5.25 inch /1.2MB Floppy Services are supported Bit 24 Int 13h - 3.5 inch / 720 KB Floppy Services are supported Bit 25 Int 13h - 3.5 inch / 2.88 MB Floppy Services are supported Bit 26 Int 5h, Print Screen Service is supported Bit 27 Int 9h, 8042 Keyboard services are supported Bit 28 Int 14h, Serial Services are supported Bit 29 Int 17h, Printer Services are supported Bit 30 Int 10h, CGA Video Services are supported Bit 31 PC-98 Bits32:47 Reserved for BIOS Vendor Bits 48:63 Reserved for System Vendor

siSerialNumber.description: This entry displays the serial number of this system.

bbManufacturer.description: This entry displays the base board manufacturer.

bbProductName.description: This entry displays the base board product name.

bbVersion.name: bbVersion
bbVersion.description: This entry displays the base board version.

bbSerialNumber.name: bbSerialNumber
bbSerialNumber.description: This entry displays the base board serial number.

mcErrorDetectingMethod.name: mcErrorDetectingMethod
mcErrorDetectingMethod.description: This entry displays the supported error detection method of the memory controller. 01h : Other 02h : Unknown 03h : None 04h : 8-bit Parity 05h : 32-bit ECC 06h : 64-bit ECC 07h : 128-bit ECC

mcErrorCorrectingCapability.name: mcErrorCorrectingCapability
mcErrorCorrectingCapability.description: This entry displays the error correcting capability of the memory controller. Bit 0 : Other Bit 1 : Unknown Bit 2 : None Bit 3 : Single Bit Error Correcting Bit 4 : Double Bit Error Correcting Bit 5 : Error Scrubbing

mcSupportedInterleave.name: mcSupportedInterleave
mcSupportedInterleave.description: This entry displays the supported memory interleave of the memory controller. 01h : Other 02h : Unknown 03h : One Way Interleave 04h : Two Way Interleave 05h : Four Way Interleave 06h : Eight Way Interleave 07h : Sixteen Way Interleave

mcCurrentInterleave.name: mcCurrentInterleave
mcCurrentInterleave.description: This entry displays the current memory interleave of the memory controller. 01h : Other 02h : Unknown 03h : One Way Interleave 04h : Two Way Interleave 05h : Four Way Interleave 06h : Eight Way Interleave 07h : Sixteen Way Interleave

mcMaximumMemoryModuleSize.name: mcMaximumMemoryModuleSize
mcMaximumMemoryModuleSize.description: This entry displays the size of the largest memory module supported (per slot), specified as n, where 2^n is the maximum size in MB.

mcSupportedSpeeds.name: mcSupportedSpeeds
mcSupportedSpeeds.description: This entry displays the supported memory speeds of the memory controller. Bit 0 : Other Bit 1 : Unknown Bit 2 : 70ns Bit 3 : 60ns Bit 4 : 50ns Bit 5-15 : Reserved, must be zero

mcSupportedMemoryTypes.name: mcSupportedMemoryTypes
mcSupportedMemoryTypes.description: This entry displays the supported memory types of the memory controller. Bit 0 : Other Bit 1 : Unknown Bit 2 : Standard Bit 3 : Fast Page Mode Bit 4 : EDO Bit 5 : Parity Bit 6 : ECC Bit 7 : SIMM Bit 8 : DIMM Bit 9-15 : Reserved, must be zero

mcMemoryModuleVoltage.name: mcMemoryModuleVoltage
mcMemoryModuleVoltage.description: This entry describes the required voltages for each of the memory module sockets controlled by the controller: Bits 7:3 Reserved, must be zero Bit 2 2.9V Bit 1 3.3V Bit 0 5V NOTE: Setting of multiple bits indicates that sockets are configurable.

mcNumberOfAssociatedMemorySlots.name: mcNumberOfAssociatedMemorySlots
mcNumberOfAssociatedMemorySlots.description: This entry defines how many of the Memory Module Information blocks are controlled by the controller.

piNumberOfProcessorInfo.name: piNumberOfProcessorInfo
piNumberOfProcessorInfo.description: This field shows the number of entries in the piProcessorInfoTable.

piProcessorInfoTable.name: piProcessorInfoTable
piProcessorInfoTable.description: This entry is a table containing information about all types of processors on the system.

piProcessorInfo.name: piProcessorInfo
piProcessorInfo.description: This entry shows information about each processor.

piSocketDesignation.name: piSocketDesignation
piSocketDesignation.description: This entry displays the processor socket designation label on top of the base board.

piProcessorType.name: piProcessorType
piProcessorType.description: This entry displays the processor type. 01H - other 02H - Unknown 03H - Central Processor 04H - Math Processor 05H - DSP Processor 06H - Video Processor

piProcessorFamily.name: piProcessorFamily
piProcessorFamily.description: This entry displays the family to which this processor belongs to. 01H - other 02H - Unknown 03H - 8086 04H - 80286 05H - 80386 06H - 80486 07H - 8087 08H - 80287 09h - 80387 0AH - 80487 0BH - Pentium Family 0CH-11H - Reserved for specific Pentium versions 12H - M1 Family 13H-18H - Reserved for specific M1 versions 19H - K5 Family 1AH-1FH - Reserved for specific K5 versions 0CH - Future X86 Class CPUs 0DH - OverDrive Family

piProcessorManufacturer.name: piProcessorManufacturer
piProcessorManufacturer.description: This entry displays the processor's manufacturer.

piProcessorID.name: piProcessorID
piProcessorID.description: This entry displays specific information which describes the processor's features. For x86 class CPUs. the field's format depends on the processor's support of the CPUID instruction. If the instruction is supported, the processor ID field contains 2 DWORD-formatted values. The first(offsets 08h - 0Bh)is the EAX value returned by a CPUID instruction with input EAX set to 1; the second(offset 0Ch-0Fh) is the EDX value returned by that instruction. Otherwise, only the first 2 bytes of the processor ID field are significant and contain the contents of the DX register at CPU reset.

piProcessorVersion.name: piProcessorVersion
piProcessorVersion.description: This entry displays the processor version.

piVoltage.name: piVoltage
piVoltage.description: This entry shows the processor's voltage requirement. Bits 7:4 Reserved, must be zero Bits 3:0 Voltage Capability. A Set bit indicates the voltage is supported. Bit 0 - 5V Bit 1 - 3.3V Bit 2 - 2.9V Bit 3 - Reserved, must be zero. Note: Setting of multiple bits indicates the socket is configurable.

piExternalClock.name: piExternalClock
piExternalClock.description: This entry shows the processor's external clock frequency in MHz. If the value is unknown, the field is set to 0.

piMaxSpeed.name: piMaxSpeed
piMaxSpeed.description: This entry shows the processor's maximum speed in MHz. If the value is unknown, the field is set to 0.

piCurrentSpeed.name: piCurrentSpeed
piCurrentSpeed.description: This entry shows the processor's current speed in MHz. If the value is unknown, the field is set to 0.

piStatus.name: piStatus
piStatus.description: This entry shows the status of this processor. Bit 6 CPU socket populated. 1 - CPU Socket Populated. 0 - CPU Socket Unpopulated. Bits 2:0 CPU Status 0h - Unknown 1h - CPU Enabled 2h - CPU disabled by user 3h - CPU disabled by system BIOS 4h - CPU is idle 5-6h Reserved 7h - Other

piProcessorUpgrade.name: piProcessorUpgrade
piProcessorUpgrade.description: This entry shows the processor upgrade method. 01h - other 02h - unknown 03h - daughter board 04h - ZIF socket 05h - replaceable piggy back 06h - None 07h - LIF socket

mmNumberOfMemoryModuleInfo.name: mmNumberOfMemoryModuleInfo
mmNumberOfMemoryModuleInfo.description: This entry shows the number of entries in the mmMemoryModuleInfoTable.

mmMemoryModuleInfoTable.name: mmMemoryModuleInfoTable
mmMemoryModuleInfoTable.description: This entry is a table containing information about all memory module sockets

mmMemoryModuleInfo.name: mmMemoryModuleInfo
mmMemoryModuleInfo.description: This entry shows information about each memory module.

mmSocketDesignation.name: mmSocketDesignation
mmSocketDesignation.description: This entry shows the memory socket designation labels on top of the base board.

mmBankConnections.name: mmBankConnections
mmBankConnections.description: This entry shows the socket to which a memory module is installed. It is a single byte value, in this byte each nibble indicates a bank(RAS#) connection, 0xF means no connection. Example: If banks 1 & 3 (RAS# 1 & 3) were connected to a SIMM socket the byte for that socket would be 13h. If only bank 2 (RAS 2) were connected the byte for that socket would be 2Fh.

mmCurrentSpeed.name: mmCurrentSpeed
mmCurrentSpeed.description: This entry shows the speed of the memory module, , in ns (e.g. 70d for a 70ns module). If the speed is unknown, the field is set to 0.

mmCurrentMemoryType.name: mmCurrentMemoryType
mmCurrentMemoryType.description: This entry shows the type of memory module currently installed: Bit 0 - other Bit 1 - unknown Bit 2 - Standard Bit 3 - Fast Page Mode Bit 4 - EDO Bit 5 - Parity Bit 6 - ECC Bit 7 - SIMM Bit 8 - DIMM Bit 9:15 Reserved, must be 0

mmInstalledSize.name: mmInstalledSize
mmInstalledSize.description: This entry shows the installed memory size. Bits 0 - 6 represent the size(n), where 2^n is the size in MB.

mmEnabledSize.name: mmEnabledSize
mmEnabledSize.description: This entry shows the enabled memory size. Bits 0 - 6 represent the size(n), where 2^n is the size in MB.

mmErrorStatus.name: mmErrorStatus
mmErrorStatus.description: This entry shows the memory error status. Bit 1 - Correctable errors received for the module Bit 0 - Uncorrectable errors received for the module

ciNumberOfCacheInfo.name: ciNumberOfCacheInfo
ciNumberOfCacheInfo.description: This field shows the number of entries in the ciCacheInfoTable.

ciCacheInfoTable.name: ciCacheInfoTable
ciCacheInfoTable.description: This entry is a table containing information about CPU cache devices.

ciCacheInfo.name: ciCacheInfo
ciCacheInfo.description: This entry shows information about each CPU cache device.

ciSocketDesignation.name: ciSocketDesignation
ciSocketDesignation.description: This entry shows the cache socket designation labels on top of the base board.

ciCacheConfiguration.name: ciCacheConfiguration
ciCacheConfiguration.description: This entry shows the configuration of this cache module. Bits 15:10 - Reserved, must be 0 Bits 9:8 - Operational Mode: 00b - Write through 01b - Write back 10b - Varies with memory address 11b - Unknown Bit 7 - Enabled/Disabled 1b - Enabled 0b - Disabled Bits 6:5 - Location 00b - Internal 01b - External 10b - Reserved 11b - Unknown Bit 4 - Reserved Bit 3 - Cache Socketed 1b - Socketed 0b - Not socketed Bits 2:0 - Cache Level

ciMaximumCacheSize.name: ciMaximumCacheSize
ciMaximumCacheSize.description: This entry shows the maximum cache size that can be installed. Bits 14:0 : Max. size in given granularity Bit 15 Granularity : 0 = 1K granularity 1 = 64K granularity

ciInstalledSize.name: ciInstalledSize
ciInstalledSize.description: This entry shows the installed cache size. Bits 14:0 : Max. size in given granularity Bit 15 Granularity : 0 = 1K granularity 1 = 64K granularity

ciSupportedSRAMType.name: ciSupportedSRAMType
ciSupportedSRAMType.description: This entry shows the supported SRAM type. Bit 0 - Other Bit 1 - Unknown Bit 2 - Nonburst Bit 3 - Burst Bit 4 - Pipeline Burst Bit 5 - Synchronous Bit 6 - Asynchronous Bits7:15 Reserved

ciCurrentSRAMType.name: ciCurrentSRAMType
ciCurrentSRAMType.description: This entry shows the current SRAM type. Bit 0 - Other Bit 1 - Unknown Bit 2 - Nonburst Bit 3 - Burst Bit 4 - Pipeline Burst Bit 5 - Synchronous Bit 6 - Asynchronous Bits7:15 Reserved

pcNumberOfPortConnectorInfo.name: pcNumberOfPortConnectorInfo
pcNumberOfPortConnectorInfo.description: This field shows the number of entries in the pcPortConnectorInfoTable

pcPortConnectorInfoTable.name: pcPortConnectorInfoTable
pcPortConnectorInfoTable.description: This entry is a table containing information about all port connectors.

pcPortConnectorInfo.name: pcPortConnectorInfo
pcPortConnectorInfo.description: This entry shows information about each port connector.

pcInternalReferenceDesignator.name: pcInternalReferenceDesignator
pcInternalReferenceDesignator.description: This entry shows the internal reference designation labels on top of the base board.

pcInternalConnectorType.name: pcInternalConnectorType
pcInternalConnectorType.description: This entry shows the internal connector type. 00h - None 01h - Centronics 02h - Mini Centronics 03h - Proprietary 04h - DB25 pin male 05h - DB25 pin female 06h - DB15 pin male 07h - DB15 pin female 08h - DB9 pin male 09h - DB9 pin female 0Ah - RJ-11 0Bh - RJ-45 0Ch - 50 pin Mini SCSI 0Dh - Mini DIN 0Eh - Micro DIN 0Fh - PS/2 10h - Infrared 11h - HP-HIL 12h - Access BUS 13h - SSA SCSI 14h - Circular DIN-8 male 15h - Circular DIN-8 female 16h - On board IDE 17h - On board floppy 18h - 9 pin dual Inline 19h - 25 pin dual Inline 1Ah - 50 pin dual Inline 1Bh - 68 pin dual Inline 1Ch - On board sound input for CD-ROM 1Dh - Mini Centronics Type 14 1Eh - Mini Centronics Type 26 A0h - PC98 A1h - PC98 Hireso A2h - PC H98 A3h - PC98 Note A4h - PC 98 Full FFh - Other

pcExternalReferenceDesignator.name: pcExternalReferenceDesignator
pcExternalReferenceDesignator.description: This entry shows the external reference designation labels on top of the base board.

pcExternalConnectorType.name: pcExternalConnectorType
pcExternalConnectorType.description: This entry shows the external connector type. 00h - None 01h - Centronics 02h - Mini Centronics 03h - Proprietary 04h - DB25 pin male 05h - DB25 pin female 06h - DB15 pin male 07h - DB15 pin female 08h - DB9 pin male 09h - DB9 pin female 0Ah - RJ-11 0Bh - RJ-45 0Ch - 50 pin Mini SCSI 0Dh - Mini DIN 0Eh - Micro DIN 0Fh - PS/2 10h - Infrared 11h - HP-HIL 12h - Access BUS 13h - SSA SCSI 14h - Circular DIN-8 male 15h - Circular DIN-8 female 16h - On board IDE 17h - On board floppy 18h - 9 pin dual Inline 19h - 25 pin dual Inline 1Ah - 50 pin dual Inline 1Bh - 68 pin dual Inline 1Ch - On board sound input for CD-ROM 1Dh - Mini Centronics Type 14 1Eh - Mini Centronics Type 26 A0h - PC98 A1h - PC98 Hireso A2h - PC H98 A3h - PC98 Note A4h - PC98 Full FFh - Other

pcPortType.name: pcPortType
pcPortType.description: This entry shows the port type 00h - None 01h - Parallel Port XT/AT Compatible 02h - Parallel Port PS/2 03h - Parallel Port ECP 04h - Parallel Port EPP 05h - Parallel Port ECP/EPP 06h - Serial Port XT/AT Compatible 07h - Serial Port 16450 Compatible 08h - Serial Port 16650 Compatible 09h - Serial Port 16650A Compatible 0Ah - SCSI Port 0Bh - MIDI Port 0Ch - Joy stick port 0Dh - Keyboard Port 0Eh - Mouse Port 0Fh - SSA SCSI 10h - USB 11h - FireWire 12h - PCMCIA Type I 13h - PCMCIA Type II 14h - PCMCIA Type III 15h - Cardbus 16h - Access Bus Port 17h - SCSI II 18h - SCSI Wide 19h - PC-98 1Ah - PC-98 Hireso 1Bh - OC-H98 A0h - 8251 Compatible A1h - 8251 FIFO Compatible FFh - Other

ssNumberOfSystemSlotInfo.name: ssNumberOfSystemSlotInfo
ssNumberOfSystemSlotInfo.description: This field shows the number of entries in ssSystemSlotInfoTable

ssSystemSlotInfoTable.name: ssSystemSlotInfoTable
ssSystemSlotInfoTable.description: This entry is a table containing information about all system slots.

ssSystemSlotInfo.name: ssSystemSlotInfo
ssSystemSlotInfo.description: This entry shows information about each system slot.

ssSlotDesignation.name: ssSlotDesignation
ssSlotDesignation.description: This entry shows the slot designation label on top of the base board.

ssSlotType.name: ssSlotType
ssSlotType.description: This entry shows the slot type. 01h - Other 02h - Unknown 03h - ISA 04h - MCA 05h - EISA 06h - PCI 07h - PCMCIA 08h - VL VESA 09h - Proprietary 0Ah - Processor Card Slot 0Bh - Proprietary Memory Card 0Ch - I/O Riser Card Slot 0Dh - NuBus 0Eh - PCI- 66MHz Capable A0h - PC98/C20 A1h - PC98/C24 A2h - PC98/E A3h - PC98/Local Bus A4h - PC98/Card

ssSlotDataBusWidth.name: ssSlotDataBusWidth
ssSlotDataBusWidth.description: This entry shows the width of the data bus. 01h - Other 02h - Unknown 03h - 8bit 04h - 16bit 05h - 32bit 06h - 64bit 07h - 128bit

ssCurrentUsage.name: ssCurrentUsage
ssCurrentUsage.description: This entry shows the current usage of this slot. 01h - Other 02h - Unknown 03h - Available 04h - In use

ssSlotLength.name: ssSlotLength
ssSlotLength.description: This entry shows the length of the slot. 01h - Other 02h - Unknown 03h - Half Length 04h - Full Length

ssSlotID.name: ssSlotID
ssSlotID.description: This entry shows the slot ID. MCA - Logical Micro Channel slot number EISA - Logical EISA slot number PCI - The value present in the slot number field of the PCI interrupt routing table entry that is associated with the slot. PCMCIA- Identifies the adapter number and socket number to be passed to PCMCIA socket services to identify this slot.

ssSlotCharacteristics.name: ssSlotCharacteristics
ssSlotCharacteristics.description: This entry shows the characteristics of this slot. Bit 0 - Unknown Bit 1 - Provide 5.0 Volts Bit 2 - Provide 3.3 Volts Bit 1 - Slot's opening is shared with another slot, e.g. PCI/EISA shared slot Bits 4:7 - Reserved

obNumberOfOnBoardDeviceInfo.name: obNumberOfOnBoardDeviceInfo
obNumberOfOnBoardDeviceInfo.description: This field shows the number of entries in the obOnBoardDeviceInfoTable.

obOnBoardDeviceInfoTable.name: obOnBoardDeviceInfoTable
obOnBoardDeviceInfoTable.description: This entry is a table containing information about all on board devices.

obOnBoardDeviceInfo.name: obOnBoardDeviceInfo
obOnBoardDeviceInfo.description: This entry shows information about each on board device.

obDeviceType.name: obDeviceType
obDeviceType.description: This entry shows the device type. 01H - Other 02H - Unknown 03H - Video 04H - SCSI 05H - Ethernet 06H - Token Ring 07H - Sound

obDescription.name: obDescription
obDescription.description: This entry shows the description of the on board device.

oemNumberOfOEMString.name: oemNumberOfOEMString
oemNumberOfOEMString.description: This field shows the number of entries in the oemStringTable.

oemStringTable.name: oemStringTable
oemStringTable.description: This entry is a table showing OEM defined strings.

oemStrings.name: oemStrings
oemStrings.description: This entry shows information about each OEM string.

oemString.name: oemString
oemString.description: This entry is an individual OEM string.

smNumberOfEventLog.name: smNumberOfEventLog
smNumberOfEventLog.description: This field shows the number of entries in the smEventLogTable.

smEventLogSupport.name: smEventLogSupport
smEventLogSupport.description: This entry shows if BIOS supports System Event Log function: 0 = NO else = YES

smEventLogTotalSize.name: smEventLogTotalSize
smEventLogTotalSize.description: This entry shows the total size of event log data area in bytes.

smEventLogUsedSize.name: smEventLogUsedSize
smEventLogUsedSize.description: This entry shows the used size of event log data area in bytes.

smEventLogUtilizationThreshold.name: smEventLogUtilizationThreshold
smEventLogUtilizationThreshold.description: This entry shows the threshold value (%) for event log data area utilization.

smEventLogTable.name: smEventLogTable
smEventLogTable.description: This entry is a table of event log entries.

smEventLogEntry.name: smEventLogEntry
smEventLogEntry.description: This entry contains information about each logged event.

smLogTime.name: smLogTime
smLogTime.description: This entry shows the event log time.

smLogType.name: smLogType
smLogType.description: This entry shows the event log type.

smLogDescription.name: smLogDescription
smLogDescription.description: This entry shows the event log description.

numberOfIPAddress.name: numberOfIPAddress
numberOfIPAddress.description: This entry shows the number of IP addresses assigned to this server.

ipAddressTable.name: ipAddressTable
ipAddressTable.description: This entry is a table showing the IP addresses assigned to this server.

ipAddresses.name: ipAddresses
ipAddresses.description: This entry shows information about each IP address assigned to this server.

ipAddress.name: ipAddress
ipAddress.description: This entry is the individual IP address assigned to this server.

ipxAddress.name: ipxAddress
ipxAddress.description: This entry is the internal IPX address assigned to this server.

numberOfLoginUser.name: numberOfLoginUser
numberOfLoginUser.description: This field shows the number of entries in the loginUserTable.

loginUserTable.name: loginUserTable
loginUserTable.description: This entry is a table containing information about all logged in users.

loginUser.name: loginUser
loginUser.description: This entry shows information about each logged in user.

loginUserName.name: loginUserName
loginUserName.description: This entry shows the logged in user's name.

loginTime.name: loginTime
loginTime.description: This entry shows the user's login time.

numberOfDriverLoaded.name: numberOfDriverLoaded
numberOfDriverLoaded.description: This field shows the number of entries in the driverLoadedTable.

driverLoadedTable.name: driverLoadedTable
driverLoadedTable.description: This entry is a table containing information about all software (including drivers) currently running on the server.

driverLoaded.name: driverLoaded
driverLoaded.description: This entry contains information about each software running on the server.

driverName.name: driverName
driverName.description: This entry shows the name of the software running on the server.

driverDescription.name: driverDescription
driverDescription.description: This entry shows a description of the software running on the server.

numberOfPageIn.name: numberOfPageIn
numberOfPageIn.description: This entry shows the number of page-ins during the last sampling.

byteOfPageIn.name: byteOfPageIn
byteOfPageIn.description: This entry shows the number of page-in bytes during the last sampling.

numberOfPageOut.name: numberOfPageOut
numberOfPageOut.description: This entry shows the number of page-out during the last sampling.

byteOfPageOut.name: byteOfPageOut
byteOfPageOut.description: This entry shows the number of page-out bytes during the last sampling.

numberOfPageFault.name: numberOfPageFault
numberOfPageFault.description: This entry shows the total number of page-faults during the last sampling.

diskCacheReadHitRatio.name: diskCacheReadHitRatio
diskCacheReadHitRatio.description: This entry shows the ratio of disk cache read hits in the last sampling.

diskCacheWriteHitRatio.name: diskCacheWriteHitRatio
diskCacheWriteHitRatio.description: This entry shows the ratio of disk cache write hits in the last sampling

numberOfFreeMem.name: numberOfFreeMem
numberOfFreeMem.description: This entry shows the number of 4KB pages available to user processes

numberOfTotalSwap.name: numberOfTotalSwap
numberOfTotalSwap.description: This entry shows the total number of physical disk (512-byte) blocks available for swapping and paging

numberOfFreeSwap.name: numberOfFreeSwap
numberOfFreeSwap.description: This entry shows the free number of physical disk (512-byte) blocks available for swapping and paging

numberOfSwapIn.name: numberOfSwapIn
numberOfSwapIn.description: This entry shows the number of transfers from swap into memory per second

numberOfSwapInPages.name: numberOfSwapInPages
numberOfSwapInPages.description: This entry shows the number of 4KB pages transfers from swap into memory per second

numberOfSwapOut.name: numberOfSwapOut
numberOfSwapOut.description: This entry shows the number of transfers from memory into swap per second. If this value is greater than zero, you may need to increase the amount of memory or reduce the number of buffers.

numberOfSwapOutPages.name: numberOfSwapOutPages
numberOfSwapOutPages.description: This entry shows the number of 4KB pages transfers from memory into swap per second

numberOfContextSwitch.name: numberOfContextSwitch
numberOfContextSwitch.description: This entry shows the number of context switch per second

physicalDiskPerfTbl.name: physicalDiskPerfTbl
physicalDiskPerfTbl.description: This entry is a table containing the performance counters of physical disk drives.

logicalDiskPerfTbl.name: logicalDiskPerfTbl
logicalDiskPerfTbl.description: This entry is a table containing the performance counters of logical disk drives.

processorTime.name: processorTime
processorTime.description: This entry is the average percentage of time all the processors on the system are busy to execute non-idle threads.

privilegedTime.name: privilegedTime
privilegedTime.description: This entry is the average percentage of time spent in Privileged mode by all processors.

userTime.name: userTime
userTime.description: This entry is the average percentage of time spent in User mode by all processors.

interruptTime.name: interruptTime
interruptTime.description: This entry is the average percentage of the Interrupt Time of all processors.

interruptsPerSec.name: interruptsPerSec
interruptsPerSec.description: This entry is the hardware interrupts received and serviced by the system per second.

contextSwitchesPerSec.name: contextSwitchesPerSec
contextSwitchesPerSec.description: This entry is the context switches from one thread to another per second.

exceptionDispatchesPerSec.name: exceptionDispatchesPerSec
exceptionDispatchesPerSec.description: This entry is the exceptions dispatched by the system per second.

systemCallsPerSec.name: systemCallsPerSec
systemCallsPerSec.description: This entry is the calls to Windows NT system service routines per second.

fileControlOpsPerSec.name: fileControlOpsPerSec
fileControlOpsPerSec.description: This entry is all file system operations that are neither reads nor writes per second.

fileControlBytesPerSec.name: fileControlBytesPerSec
fileControlBytesPerSec.description: This entry is bytes transferred for all file system operations that are neither reads nor writes per second.

fileDataOpsPerSec.name: fileDataOpsPerSec
fileDataOpsPerSec.description: This entry is the read and write operations to file system devices per second.

fileReadOpsPerSec.name: fileReadOpsPerSec
fileReadOpsPerSec.description: This entry is the read operations of all the file system per second.

fileWriteOpsPerSec.name: fileWriteOpsPerSec
fileWriteOpsPerSec.description: This entry is the number of write operations of all the file system per second.

fileReadBytesPerSec.name: fileReadBytesPerSec
fileReadBytesPerSec.description: This entry is the bytes transferred for all the file system read operations per second.

fileWriteBytesPerSec.name: fileWriteBytesPerSec
fileWriteBytesPerSec.description: This entry is the bytes transferred for all the file system write operations per second.

copyReadsHitRatio.name: copyReadsHitRatio
copyReadsHitRatio.description: This entry is the percentage of Cache Copy Read requests that hit the cache.

copyReadsPerSec.name: copyReadsPerSec
copyReadsPerSec.description: This entry is the number of copy reads per second.

dataMapHitRatio.name: dataMapHitRatio
dataMapHitRatio.description: This entry is the percentage of Data Maps in the cache.

dataMapsPerSec.name: dataMapsPerSec
dataMapsPerSec.description: This entry is the frequency (per second) that a file system maps a page of a file into the cache to read the page.

dataFlushesPerSec.name: dataFlushesPerSec
dataFlushesPerSec.description: This entry is the frequency (per second) that the cache has flushed its contents to disk. More than one page can be transferred on each flush operation.

dataFlushPagesPerSec.name: dataFlushPagesPerSec
dataFlushPagesPerSec.description: This entry is the number of pages per second the cache has flushed to disk. More than one page can be transferred on each flush operation.

lazeWriteFlushesPerSec.name: lazeWriteFlushesPerSec
lazeWriteFlushesPerSec.description: This entry is the frequency (per second) that the cache's Lazy Write thread has written to disk. More than one page can be transferred on each write operation.

lazeWritePagesPerSec.name: lazeWritePagesPerSec
lazeWritePagesPerSec.description: This entry is the frequency (per second) the cache's Lazy Write thread has written to disk. More than one page can be transferred on a single disk write operation.

pageFaultsPerSec.name: pageFaultsPerSec
pageFaultsPerSec.description: This entry is the number of page faults per second in the processor.

transitionFaultsPerSec.name: transitionFaultsPerSec
transitionFaultsPerSec.description: This entry is the number of page faults resolved per second by recovering pages that were in transition. The pages were recovered without additional disk activity.

writeCopiesPerSec.name: writeCopiesPerSec
writeCopiesPerSec.description: This entry is the number of page faults per second that have been satisfied by making a copy of a page when an attempt to write to the page is made.

pageReadPerSec.name: pageReadPerSec
pageReadPerSec.description: This entry is the number of times the disk was read per second to retrieve pages of virtual memory necessary to resolve page faults. Multiple pages can be read during a disk read operation.

pageWritePerSec.name: pageWritePerSec

pagesPerSec.name: pagesPerSec

fuseStatus.name: fuseStatus
fuseStatus.description: This entry displays the status of fuses. Each bit indicates separate status of one fuse, 1 is failed, 0 is noraml. If system has no fuse at all, the entry shows -1. bit0: Keyboard/Mouse fuse bit1: USB1 fuse bit2: USB2 fuse bit3: SCSI1 fuse bit4: SCSI2 fuse

redundantPowerSupplyStatus.name: redundantPowerSupplyStatus
redundantPowerSupplyStatus.description: This entry displays the status of redundant power subsystem. If system has no such equipment installed, bit31 of this value will be set to 1. fanTable.name: fanTable
fanTable.description: This entry is a table containing information about all fans.

fanLocation.description: This entry shows the fan's location in the server system, e.g. 'CPU1', 'CPU2' or 'HOUSING'.

fanStatus.description: This entry displays the fan's working status: 0=normal 1=abnormal. When the fan is not rotating or is not installed, the status will be considered abnormal.

fanRPM.name: fanRPM
fanRPM.description: This entry displays the fan's rotation speed in RPM. If the fan doesn't provide RPM information, the value will be -1.

thermometerInfo.description: This entry contains information about each thermometer.

thermometerLocation.description: This entry shows the thermometer's location in the server system, e.g. 'CPU1', 'CPU2' or 'SYSTEM'.

voltageTable.name: voltageTable

voltageLocation.description: This entry shows the voltage sensor's location in the server system, e.g. 'CPU1', 'CPU2' or 'SYSTEM'.

validVoltage.name: validVoltage
validVoltage.description: This entry displays the ideal voltage reading in milli-volts.

maxVoltage.name: maxVoltage
maxVoltage.description: This entry displays the maximum safe operating voltage in milli-volts. If the voltage goes above this value, the system may not work properly.

minVoltage.name: minVoltage

busCounterInfo.description: This entry contains information about each bus utilization counter.

busCounterLocation.description: The system bus monitored by the counter e.g. 'PCI1', 'PCI2', 'EISA1' or 'EISA2'.

busUtilization.name: busUtilization
busUtilization.description: This entry displays the bus utilization. Values displayed have to be divided by one hundred (100) to show the percentage of bus utilization. For example, a reading of 1234 means that bus utilization is at 12.34%.

cpuSlotStatus.name: cpuSlotStatus
cpuSlotStatus.description: This entry is partitioned into nibbles, each shows status of one CPU slot: bit0: CPU is present bit1: CPU is enabled bit2: CPU error (IERR#, Thermtrip# issued).

upsPower2Exist.description: This entry shows the power supply condition: 1 = power supply #2 exists 0 = power supply #2 doesn't exist.

upsPower3Exist.description: This entry shows the power supply condition: 1 = power supply #3 exists 0 = power supply #3 doesn't exist.
